    {
        "content": "<p>So <code>@show</code> shows unevaluated code on the LHS and the evaluation result on the RHS... and you want the same RHS, but LHS to have just the variables evaluated, not the whole expression. <br>\nThat sounds like an unorthodox requirement, seems unlikely there'd be a standard macro for this already.</p>",
        "id": 262163190,
        "sender_full_name": "Sundar R",
        "timestamp": 1637384038
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"423970\">@Sundar R</span>  OK <span aria-label=\"pray\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f64f\" role=\"img\" title=\"pray\">:pray:</span> - makes sense.<br>\nI‚Äôll see if anyone else has an idea, otherwise I‚Äôll enjoy another diversion, and learn to write macros. Of-course from where I am, I can't tell if this is feasible yet.</p>",
        "id": 262163752,
